SIMPLE: graceful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graceful
<hw>Grace"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Displaying grace or
beauty in form or action; elegant; easy; agreeable in appearance;
<as>as, a <ex>graceful</ex> walk, deportment, speaker, air, act,
speech</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>High o'er the rest in arms the <qex>graceful</qex> Turnus
rode.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Grace"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<wf>Grace"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graceless</ent>⟦br⟧
